/**
 * Gate 1 of the title/skill semantic-matching investigation (see
 * gate2-title-skill-matching-cascade-spec.md) - 18 queries across 9
 * categories, adjudicated by the product owner (not just LLM-generated and
 * accepted) before being folded into LABELED_QUERIES. This is the baseline
 * Gate 2's cascade gets measured and calibrated against.
 *
 * Provenance: generated by 9 parallel LLM agents, each producing 2 queries
 * with explicit instructions to work in the specific collision cases both
 * the skillAliases and titleAliases adversarial audits already found (Real
 * Estate Developer, Medical Coder, NLP acronym collision, onboarding
 * product-vs-HR, SOC2-vs-legal compliance, P&L literacy-vs-ownership,
 * EMR-vs-EHR, sales-QA-vs-tech-QA, SEM/CRO acronym collisions, etc.) as
 * concrete hard-negative or partial-credit foils, not generic ones.
 * labeledBy is 'llm-judge:claude-sonnet-5' - the SAME model family building
 * the matcher these labels calibrate, a real correlated-bias risk. The
 * mitigation actually applied: full human adjudication of every flagged
 * judgment call plus a manual sweep of the whole set (grade change, two
 * structural fixes below) - not just accepting the LLM output.
 *
 * Adjudication changes from the raw generation:
 * - product-management-gate1-2's "teamleiter produktentwicklung" downgraded
 *   4->... no: 3->2. In the German market "Produktentwicklung" reads as the
 *   engineering/R&D department, and the job's own tags confirm it (Cross-
 *   functional Leadership, Team Building, OKRs - zero product-strategy/
 *   roadmap signal): a line-management posting, not an adjacent PM role.
 *   Grading it 3 would reward treating Stakeholder Management and
 *   Cross-functional Leadership as near-synonyms - the exact over-collapse
 *   the skillAliases audit already rejected. The eval must encode that
 *   ruling, not quietly relitigate it.
 * - Hard-negative status is now a structured `isHardNegative` field (see
 *   types.ts), not a prose convention - the raw generation's prose-only
 *   flagging undercounted by one and cannot feed a harness invariant.
 * - Restored proper German orthography (a/o/u-umlaut, sharp s) throughout -
 *   the first transcription pass silently stripped every diacritic from
 *   matcher-visible fields (jobTitleNormalized/techStackTags), which meant
 *   the German leg never exercised diacritic normalization or Tier 2's
 *   planned exact-match against ESCO's German alternative labels (which do
 *   carry diacritics) at all.
 * - Added two new title entries that carry diacritics pre-normalization
 *   (Geschaftsfuhrer Vertrieb, Aussendienstmitarbeiter - see
 *   sales-gate1-2) specifically to close that gap, not just fix existing
 *   entries.
 *
 * Gate 2 calibration note (from adjudication): the seniority-collapse rows
 * (VP of Engineering, Experimentation Platform Manager, Bereichsleiter mit
 * P&L-Verantwortung, EHR Interoperability Specialist) all test the
 * COMPOSITE score. The seniority dimension must be what punishes these, not
 * the title/skill layer itself - tuning Tier 2's cascade to also encode
 * seniority would double-penalize the same gap twice.
 */
